Jacek nam napisał:

1. Apache mod_rewrite is not enabled

Laravel routing depends on URL rewriting so mod_rewrite must be enabled.

How to check and enable:

sudo a2enmod rewrite
sudo systemctl restart apache2


2. AllowOverride Not set to All

Apache needs to allow .htaccess to override settings.

Check your virtual host configuration, usually in:

/etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf

Or:

/etc/apache2/apache2.conf

Make sure the <Directory> directive looks like this:

<Directory /var/www/html/your-laravel-project/public>
    AllowOverride All
</Directory>

Then reload Apache:

sudo systemctl restart apache2


Wrong DocumentRoot

Laravel’s entry point is the public folder. If Apache is pointing to the Laravel root instead of public, routing will break.

3. Ensure your VirtualHost has:

DocumentRoot /var/www/html/your-laravel-project/public

…and not:

DocumentRoot /var/www/html/your-laravel-project

Otherwise, Laravel’s index.php won’t be used properly


4.  .htaccess file is missing or misconfigured

Laravel comes with a .htaccess inside public/. Make sure it exists and looks something like this:

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteRule ^(.*)$ public/$1 [L]
</IfModule>

or (more commonly) this:

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    <IfModule mod_negotiation.c>
        Options -MultiViews -Indexes
    </IfModule>

    RewriteEngine On

    # Redirect Trailing Slashes...
    RewriteRule ^(.*)/$ /$1 [L,R=301]

    # Handle Front Controller...
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
    RewriteRule ^ index.php [L]
</IfModule>

Verify it exists and has correct rules

5. Permissions Issue

If Apache can’t read the files inside public, routing will fail.

Fix permissions:

sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/html/your-laravel-project
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/your-laravel-project/storage
sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html/your-laravel-project/bootstrap/cache

6. Apache Overrides Disabled Globally

In apache2.conf, ensure this block is not overriding your site:

<Directory /var/www/>
    AllowOverride All
</Directory>

7. Quick Test

After you check all the above:

    Restart Apache

    Clear Laravel caches:

php artisan config:cache
php artisan route:cache
php artisan view:cache

    Try accessing routes again.


